<TITLE> BCL leader killed, 5 hurt in Mirpur shooting </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 13 (bdnews24.com)One person was killed and five injured when assailants opened fire in Mirpur's Swadheen Bangla Market on Monday, police said. Assistant police commissioner Moinul Hasan told bdnews24.com that around 3pm, three to four men drove up to the market at Mirpur-10 and opened fire, striking people lounging in front of a tile emporium. The men then fled the scene on motorcycles, according to witnesses. Former Chhatra League leader Abdur Rahim, 40, and five others were wounded by the gunfire. Rahim died as he was being transported to Dhaka Medical College Hospital. The other five men were admitted to DMCH. Two of the wounded are reportedly in critical condition. Protesting the incident, BCL leaders and activists of the nearby Bangla College took to the streets to demand the arrest of the attackers. Traffic movement along Darus Salam Road was disrupted as a result of the demonstration. bdnews2
